Voir Dire List
Random Listing Report - Voir Dire.

Defendant Maxwell L Fry in court with attorney Katie B. Bricco and Attorney Kelsey Moran.  Ted Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Court addresses the jury instructions, motion in limine, witnesses (housekeeping issues).  The trial is expected to last one day.  There will be a total of 12 jurors chosen.  Each side will be allowed 4 strikes each.  The witnesses will be excluded during the testimony.  The Court will permit note taking by the jurors and the Court will allow juror questions.   Charging language agreed on by both parties.  Jurors enter the Courtroom at 9:00 a.m.   The Court presents introductory remarks.   Clerk swears in panel of jurors.  Court conducts voir dire.  Kim M. and Laurel K. struck for cause.  Clerk calls next potential jurors.   Counsel exercise 4 strikes each.  12 Jurors are selected to try the issues.  The balance of the jurors return to the JAR.  The Clerk swears in the selected jurors.   Jurors removed and Court is in recess 10:04 a.m. Court reconvenes at 10:15 a.m.   The jurors enter the Courtroom.  The Court presents preliminary instructions to the jurors.  The State presents its opening statements.  Attorney Bricco presents its opening statements. The State calls its first witness: Detective Andy Jicha with the City of Waukesha Police Department is sworn in and testified.  The State conducts direct examination of the witness.   Exhibit #1 is marked and presented to the witness.  The State moves for admission of the Exhibit.  The Court admits Exhibit #1 into evidence.  Exhibit #1 is published to the jury.  Exhibit 2 is marked and presented to the witness.  The State moves for admission of the Exhibit.  The Court admits Exhibit #2 into evidence.  Exhibit #2 is published to the jury.  Exhibit #3 is marked and presented to the witness.  The State moves for admission of the Exhibit.  The Court admits Exhibit #3 into evidence.  Exhibit #3 is published to the jury.  Attorney Bricco conducts cross examination of the witness.  Exhibit #100 is marked and presented to the witness.  Attorney Bricco moves for admission of Exhibit.  The Court admits Exhibit #100 into evidence. The State conducts re-direct of the witness.  Re-cross of the witness by Attorney Bricco.  A question is submitted by the jury to the witness.  The Jurors are excused at 11:48 a.m. The parties are excused at 11:52 p.m. for lunch break for and to reconvene at 1:15 p.m.  The Court reconvenes at 1:15 p.m. outside the presence of the jurors.  The jurors enter the Courtroom at 1:17 p.m.  The State calls its next witness Detective Probst with the City of Waukesha Police Department to the stand.  The witness is sworn in and testifies.  The State conducts direct examination of the witness.  Attorney Bricco conducts cross examination of the witness.  Exhibits #101 and #102 are marked and presented to the witness.  Attorney Bricco moves for admission of Exhibits.  The Court admits Exhibits #101 and #102 into evidence.  The exhibits are published to the jurors.  Cross examination of the Witness by Attorney Bricco.  The witness is excused.  The State rests.  Attorney Bricco motions the Court to dismiss.  The Court denies the motion. The Court takes a brief break at 2:03 p.m.     The Court reconvenes outside the presence of the jurors.   The Court conducts plea colloquy with the Defendant.  The Defendant will testify.   The jurors enter the Courtroom at 2:10 p.m.  The Defense calls its first witness, the Defendant to the stand.  The witness is sworn in.  Attorney Bricco conducts direct examination of the witness.  The State conducts cross examination of the witness. Re-direct by Attorney Bricco. Re-cross by the State.  The witness is excused.  The Jurors are excused at 3:50 p.m.  The Court reconvenes at 4:05 p.m. outside the presence of the jurors.  The Court reviews jury instructions.  The jurors enter the Courtroom at 4:30 p.m.   The State and Defense both rest.  The State presents closing arguments.  The Defense presents closing arguments.  The State presents brief rebuttal arguments.  The Court reads the jury instructions to the jurors.  The Court swears in the bailiff in charge of the jurors. Jurors retire to the jury room for deliberation at 5:17 p.m.  The Court reconvenes at 5:40 p.m. The jurors reached a verdict at 5:45 p.m. Jurors find the Defendant guilty on Count 1.  Defense does request juurors be polled. The Court polls the jurors.  The State moves for judgment on the verdicts.  The Court enters judgment on the verdicts.   The Court revokes bail and the Defendant is taken into custody forthwith.  The Court sets the matter for sentencing.
